verses.text: My son , if thou be surety for thy friend , \add if\add* thou hast stricken thy hand with a stranger ,
Thou art snared with the words of thy mouth , thou art taken with the words of thy mouth.

Do this now , my son , and deliver thyself, when thou art come into the hand of thy friend ; go , humble thyself, and make sure thy friend.\f + \fr 6.3 \ft and make…: or, so shalt thou prevail with thy friend\f*
Give not sleep to thine eyes , nor slumber to thine eyelids.
Deliver thyself as a roe from the hand \add of the hunter\add*, and as a bird from the hand of the fowler. \p
¶ Go to the ant , thou sluggard ; consider her ways , and be wise :
Which having no guide , overseer , or ruler ,
Provideth her meat in the summer , \add and\add* gathereth her food in the harvest.
How long wilt thou sleep , O sluggard ? when wilt thou arise out of thy sleep ?
\add Yet\add* a little sleep , a little slumber , a little folding of the hands to sleep :
So shall thy poverty come as one that travelleth , and thy want as an armed man. \p
¶ A naughty person , a wicked man , walketh with a froward mouth.
He winketh with his eyes , he speaketh with his feet , he teacheth with his fingers ;
Frowardness \add is\add* in his heart , he deviseth mischief continually ; he soweth discord.\f + \fr 6.14 \ft soweth: Heb. casteth forth\f*
Therefore shall his calamity come suddenly ; suddenly shall he be broken without remedy. \p
¶ These six \add things\add* doth the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* hate : yea, seven \add are\add* an abomination unto him :\f + \fr 6.16 \ft unto…: Heb. of his soul\f*
A proud look , a lying tongue , and hands that shed innocent blood ,\f + \fr 6.17 \ft A proud…: Heb. Haughty eyes\f*
An heart that deviseth wicked imaginations , feet that be swift in running to mischief ,
A false witness \add that\add* speaketh lies , and he that soweth discord among brethren. \p
¶ My son , keep thy father’s commandment , and forsake not the law of thy mother :
Bind them continually upon thine heart , \add and\add* tie them about thy neck.
When thou goest , it shall lead thee; when thou sleepest , it shall keep thee; and \add when\add* thou awakest , it shall talk with thee.
For the commandment \add is\add* a lamp ; and the law \add is\add* light ; and reproofs of instruction \add are\add* the way of life :\f + \fr 6.23 \ft lamp: or, candle\f*
To keep thee from the evil woman , from the flattery of the tongue of a strange woman.\f + \fr 6.24 \ft of the…: or, of the strange tongue\f*
Lust not after her beauty in thine heart ; neither let her take thee with her eyelids.

For by means of a whorish woman \add a man is brought\add* to a piece of bread : and the adulteress will hunt for the precious life.\f + \fr 6.26 \ft the adulteress: Heb. the woman of a man, or, a man’s wife\f*
Can a man take fire in his bosom , and his clothes not be burned ?
Can one go upon hot coals , and his feet not be burned ?
So he that goeth in to his neighbour’s wife ; whosoever toucheth her shall not be innocent.
\add Men\add* do not despise a thief , if he steal to satisfy his soul when he is hungry ;
But \add if\add* he be found , he shall restore sevenfold ; he shall give all the substance of his house.
\add But\add* whoso committeth adultery with a woman lacketh understanding : he \add that\add* doeth it destroyeth his own soul.\f + \fr 6.32 \ft understanding: Heb. heart\f*
A wound and dishonour shall he get ; and his reproach shall not be wiped away.
For jealousy \add is\add* the rage of a man : therefore he will not spare in the day of vengeance.
He will not regard any ransom ; neither will he rest content , though thou givest many gifts.\f + \fr 6.35 \ft He will…: Heb. He will not accept the face of any ransom\f*
